Constructor Detail

DocumentImpl

public DocumentImpl(org.w3c.dom.Document document)
Protected constructors that take a DOM document object but not an element object are used for generating new element nodes in a NeXML document. On calling such constructors, a new element is created, which can be retrieved using getElement(). After this step, the Impl class that called this constructor would still need to attach the element in the proper location (typically as a child element of the class that called the constructor).

Parameters:
document - a DOM document object

DocumentImpl

public DocumentImpl(org.w3c.dom.Document document,
                    org.w3c.dom.Element element)
This is the only public constructor that takes an element as its argument. This is so that we can start the recursive element traversal from outside this packages, e.g. in the DocumentFactory.

Parameters:
document - the containing DOM document object. Every Impl class needs a reference to this so that it can create DOM element objects
element - the root element

public TreeBlock createTreeBlock(OTUs otus)

createCategoricalMatrix

public CategoricalMatrix createCategoricalMatrix(OTUs otus)
This method creates the characters element and appends it to the document root. Because NeXML requires that characters elements have an id reference attribute to specify the otus element it refers to, the equivalent OTUs object needs to be passed in here. In addition, characters elements need to specify the concrete subclass they implement (the xsi:type business). XXX Here, this subclass is set to StandardCells. Hopefully we come up with a better way to do this.

Specified by:
createCategoricalMatrix in interface Document
Parameters:
otus - a taxa block
Returns:
a character state matrix

                                             java.lang.String type)
Description copied from interface: Document
Creates a new molecular character matrix, i.e. a matrix of type DNA|RNA|Protein*. All rows in the matrix must refer to an OTU from the provided taxa block

Specified by:
createMolecularMatrix in interface Document

In addition, characters elements need to specify the concrete subclass they implement (the xsi:type business). XXX Here, this subclass is set to a molecular sequence type as specified in param type. getAnnotationValues

public java.util.Set<java.lang.Object> getAnnotationValues(java.lang.String property)
Description copied from interface: Annotatable
For a single annotation property (i.e. a predicate), multiple annotation values may be returned. These could be literal text content of a meta element, a resource identifier (e.g. a url defined by the href attribute value), and/or recursively nested meta annotations or other xml. This method returns all of these.
